{"image_id": "DOV_2014_page_92", "image_size": [1238, 1613], "ocr": [{"text": "88", "bbox": [608.6, 1533.4, 629.4, 1556.5]}, {"text": "are in compliance with ERISA, other relevant legislation, and related plan documents.  Where relevant, the Company has retained", "bbox": [93.8, 117.3, 1149.5, 140.4]}, {"text": "professional investment managers to manage the plans’ assets and implement the investment process. The investment managers,", "bbox": [93.8, 142.4, 1149.7, 165.4]}, {"text": "in implementing their investment processes, have the authority and responsibility to select appropriate investments in the asset", "bbox": [93.8, 167.4, 1149.5, 190.4]}, {"text": "classes specified by the terms of their applicable prospectus or investment manager agreements with the plans.", "bbox": [93.8, 192.4, 1015.2, 215.4]}, {"text": "The assets of the plans are invested to achieve an appropriate return for the plans consistent with a prudent level of risk. The", "bbox": [93.8, 242.4, 1149.5, 265.5]}, {"text": "asset return objective is to achieve, as a minimum over time, the passively managed return earned by market index funds,", "bbox": [93.8, 267.4, 1149.6, 290.5]}, {"text": "weighted in the proportions outlined by the asset class exposures identified in the plans’ strategic allocation.  The expected return", "bbox": [93.8, 292.4, 1149.4, 315.5]}, {"text": "on assets assumption used for pension expense is developed through analysis of historical market returns, statistical analysis,", "bbox": [93.8, 317.4, 1149.5, 340.5]}, {"text": "current market conditions, and the past experience of plan asset investments. Overall, it is projected that the investment of plan", "bbox": [93.8, 342.4, 1149.4, 365.5]}, {"text": "assets within Dover’s U.S. defined benefit plan will achieve a 7.75% net return over time from the asset allocation strategy.", "bbox": [93.8, 367.4, 1121.9, 390.5]}, {"text": "The Company’s actual and target weighted-average asset allocation for our U.S. Corporate Pensi